&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Faire&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Faire is a technology wholesale platform built on the belief that the future is local. Independent retailers around the globe collectively represent a multi-hundred-billion-dollar wholesale market that has historically been fragmented and offline. At Faire, we&#39;re using the power of tech, data, and machine learning to connect this thriving community of entrepreneurs across the globe. Picture your favorite boutique in town — we help them discover the best products from around the world to sell in their stores. With the right tools and insights, we believe that we can level the playing field so businesses can grow and local communities can thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for smart, resourceful and passionate people to join us as we power the shop local movement. If you believe in community, come join ours.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Faire is seeking Senior Technical Program Managers to lead some of the company’s most critical and cross-functional initiatives. As part of a highly leveraged TPM team, you’ll work across domains—spanning infrastructure, data, AI/ML, product engineering, and platform efficiency—to accelerate execution, improve alignment, and deliver measurable business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll partner with senior leaders across Engineering, Product, and Business to define strategy, translate technical complexity into clear plans, and drive programs from concept to completion. This role requires strong technical aptitude, systems thinking, and the ability to quickly understand new domains to guide teams toward successful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead high-impact, cross-functional programs that span multiple technical and business areas—from planning through delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering and product leadership to define goals, milestones, and success metrics aligned with company priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop clear execution strategies, manage dependencies, and proactively surface risks and tradeoffs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and evolve scalable program management practices that increase delivery speed and quality.&lt;br&gt;Contribute to strategic planning and prioritization through data-driven insights and structured execution frameworks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant technical program or project management experience driving cross-functional initiatives in software or platform engineering environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record delivering large-scale, complex programs with measurable business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical fluency and ability to quickly understand new systems, architectures, and problem spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and influencing skills across technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
